# CATCH environment variables
#
# CATCH deploys as a fully static site and needs NO secrets: there is no database,
# API key, or server credential at runtime. The only variable is an optional build-time
# path prefix for hosting under a sub-path.

# Base path for the deployment, injected at BUILD time (not runtime).
#   - Vercel / custom domain / root hosting:  leave empty (the default)
#   - GitHub project pages (user.github.io/<repo>):  set to "/<repo>"
# The GitHub Pages workflow sets this automatically from the repo name; you normally
# never set it by hand. Must be prefixed NEXT_PUBLIC_ so the browser bundle can read it.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_PATH=/catch
